headline: Expedia Stock Gets a New Buy Rating. What’s Behind the Call.
summary: Expedia Group  stock is a Buy thanks to improving travel trends,  BofA  Securities said on Wednesday.  Analysts Justin Post and Harvey Qin upgraded shares of the online travel agency to Buy from Neutral and increased their price target to $221 from $187.  Expedia stock gained 2.1% to $184.42 in late morning trading.

headline: Expedia Stock Gains After Analyst Upgrade Sees Improving U.S. Travel Trends
summary: Expedia Group stock gained Wednesday morning after BofA Securities analysts boosted their outlook on the stock to buy from neutral.  BofA analyst Justin Post also raised his price target for Expedia to 221, from 187, in the client note early Wednesday.  Post added that he was previously cautious because Expedia consumer-focused nights booking growth was growing slower compared to its larger competitor Booking Holdings, as well as the growth rate for Airbnb.
